      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The right strategy depends on the conversation pattern. For focused, short conversations, a sliding window is usually sufficient. For long-running, information-dense sessions (legal document review, extended coding sessions), summarisation prevents context saturation. For cross-session personalisation, vector memory is the only scalable option."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Privacy and Compliance Considerations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Stateful systems store user data, which creates obligations that stateless systems do not have."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Data minimisation",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": store only what is needed. If only the last 6 turns are used for the next response, there is no operational reason to retain the full 200-turn history permanently."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Retention limits",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": define and enforce session TTLs. Expired sessions should be automatically evicted from the session store and from any persistent log store. Implement "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "evict_expired()",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " as a scheduled job, not just at read time."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Right to erasure",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": GDPR Article 17 requires that a user's data be deleted on request. Vector memory and session stores must support deletion by user ID, not just by session ID."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Encryption at rest",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": session data stored in Redis or a database should be encrypted. If the conversation contains PII, use field-level encryption on the message content."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Cross-user isolation",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": every session lookup must be gated by user ID, not just session ID. A bug that allows user A to read user B's session history is a data breach."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
